Package neupaths.api

Class Cell

java.lang.Object
neupaths.api.Cell
Direct Known Subclasses:
BridgeCell, EventCell, ExtractorCell, InjectorCell, LogicCell, RouterCell
public class Cell extends Object
The base class for NeuPaths cell types. Provides accessor methods for common cell characteristics and methods to control the event logging facilities.

Logging Facilities

User-level logging (EventType values AUDIT 1-9, INFORMATION, WARNING and ERROR) is enabled for cells by default. Runtime, Trace and Debug logging are disabled by default. The DEBUG and TRACE event types can also be used by NeuPaths API clients. The Activator logEvent methods can be used in API client code, but event stimuli will not be produced unless the corresponding logging is enabled.

Performance Tuning

A cell system is a dynamic entity. Since a system can change at any time, it is necessary to periodically advertise subscriptions. A cell's subscription refresh interval determines how frequently the cell advertises its subscriptions. In a large system, subscription refreshes can add significantly to system traffic. Use the setSubscriptionRefreshInterval(long) method to tune a cell's subscription refresh interval.

Complex cell systems may contain redundant communication paths. This can lead to delivery of duplicate stimuli. A cell must maintain a journal of recently received stimuli in order to detect duplicates. Such a journal can consume resources. Use the setDuplicateDetectionInterval(long) method to tune a cell's duplicate detection interval.

    • setDuplicateDetectionInterval

      public void setDuplicateDetectionInterval(long millisecs)
      Sets the duplicate detection interval.

      The default is 1000 milliseconds (1 second.) The minimum is 250 milliseconds. Values less than the minimum will be automatically changed to the minimum value.

      Parameters:
      millisecs - Duration of interval in milliseconds

    • setSubscriptionRefreshInterval

      public void setSubscriptionRefreshInterval(long millisecs)
      Sets the subscription refresh interval.

      The default is 1500 milliseconds (1.5 seconds.) Values less than or equal to zero will disable automatic subscription refreshes. When disabled, the user must manually invoke publishSubscriptions() to advertise the cell's subscriptions.

      Parameters:
      millisecs - Duration of interval in milliseconds

    • setSubscriptionTraceInterval

      public void setSubscriptionTraceInterval(long millisecs)
      Sets the subscription trace interval.

      When enabled, the cell's nucleus reports the subscriptions it has registered in an EventType.TRACE log event each interval. Values less than or equal to zero disable subscription tracing. The value is zero by default, meaning this feature must be specifically enabled.

      Parameters:
      millisecs - Duration of interval in milliseconds

    • publishSubscriptions

      public void publishSubscriptions()
      Advertises the cell's subscriptions to the cell system. This method can be used when subscription refresh has been turned off. It should only be invoked after the cell has been started.
